Hi,  
At client side Instead of CallCalculator().Wait(), how can we delagate result to another function( like old callback functions)...  
I try the following,  
async Task CallCalculator()  
 {  
 try  
 {  

 var task = channel.DivideAsync(10, 0);  

 task.ContinueWith(OnWorkCompleted); //You should see result at OnWorkCompleted  

 }  
 catch (FaultException ex)  
 {  
 Console.Error.WriteLine("Error: " + ex.Detail.Message);  
 }  

 }  

 void OnWorkCompleted(Task task)  
 {  

 var result = task.Result;  

 Console.WriteLine("Result From Async: " + result);  
}  

It works but if we try to divide by zero, I do not catch any exception at client side.

When i put this in my service the EndCreateTrafficAlerts method is never called. When I set a breakpoint on the callback(tcs.Task) line, I can see it get hit but nothing happens.  
In client;  
public static Task CreateTrafficAlertsAsync(this Release2Client client, IEnumerable trafficIds, TrafficMasterAlert alert, Release release )  
 {  
 return Task.Factory.FromAsync(client.Contract.BeginCreateTrafficAlerts, client.Contract.EndCreateTrafficAlerts, trafficIds, alert, release);  
 }  

In server:  
public IAsyncResult BeginCreateTrafficAlerts(IEnumerable trafficIds, TrafficMasterAlert masterAlert, AsyncCallback callback, object state)  
 {  
 try  
 {  
 var creator = new TrafficAlertsCreator();  
 var task = creator.BeginCreateTrafficAlerts(trafficIds, masterAlert);  
 var tcs = new TaskCompletionSource(this);  
 task.ContinueWith(t =>  
 {  
 if (t.IsFaulted)  
 {  
 if (t.Exception != null) tcs.TrySetException(t.Exception.InnerExceptions);  
 }  
 else if (t.IsCanceled)  
 tcs.TrySetCanceled();  
 else  
 tcs.TrySetResult(t.Result);  
 if (callback != null)  
 callback(tcs.Task);  
 });  
 return tcs.Task;  
 }  
 catch (Exception exc)  
 {  
 Log.Error(exc);  
 throw new FaultException(exc.Message);  
 }  
 }  

 public bool EndCreateTrafficAlerts(IAsyncResult ar)  
 {  
 try  
 {  
 MethodLogger.LogMethodCall("Started to execute method", MethodBase.GetCurrentMethod(), ar);  
 ar.AsyncWaitHandle.WaitOne();  
 var task = (Task) ar;  
 task.Wait();  
 var creator = (TrafficAlertsCreator) task.AsyncState;  
 return creator.EndCreateTrafficAlerts(ar);  
 }  
 catch (FaultException)  
 {  
 throw; //just rethrow  
 }  
 catch (Exception ex)  
 {  
 Log.Error("An error occurred in the EndCreateTrafficAlerts method", ex);  
 throw new FaultException(ex.Message);  
 }  
 finally  
 {  
 MethodLogger.LogMethodCall("Completed executing method", MethodBase.GetCurrentMethod(), ar);  
 }  

 }

Thanks Stephen, I think something like this:

public static async Task<tresult> UsingAsync<t, tresult="">(this T client, Func<t, task<tresult="">> work) where T : ICommunicationObject  
 {  
 TResult result;  
 try  
 {  
 result = await work(client);  
 client.Close();  
 }  
 catch (CommunicationException)  
 {  
 client.Abort();  
 throw;  
 }  
 catch (TimeoutException)  
 {  
 client.Abort();  
 throw;  
 }  
 catch (Exception)  
 {  
 client.Abort();  
 throw;  
 }  
 return result;  
 }

